xgetopt (0.12.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Removed macros, instantiate via template programming
    The XGETOPT_PARSER and XGETOPT_OPTION macros have been removed.
    Users should now instantiate OptionParser directly using template
    parameters for each Option.
  * Compile-time guarantees: no duplicate short/long options within a single
    parser instance.
    If two options *in the same parser* share the same short or long option,
    a static_assert will trigger at compile-time.
    Without this, duplicate options would lead to undefined behavior at runtime
    when parsed by GNU getopt.

 -- rail5 <andrew@rail5.org>  Tue, 10 Feb 2026 08:52:39 +0800

