 -- rail5 <andrew@rail5.org>  Fri, 06 Feb 2026 20:12:50 +0800

xgetopt (0.11.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Refactor:
    Implemented compile-time calculation of help string buffer size.
    Use FixedString and OptionView for constexpr string and option handling.
    Removed legacy Option and FixedString implementations.
    Improved internal option label formatting logic.
  * Added support for argument placeholders in help output (e.g., <file> for
    output).
  * Added getOptions() method to retrieve defined options.
  * Improved help string formatting:
    Required arguments now display as <placeholder>.
    Optional arguments for long options display as [=placeholder], matching GNU
    conventions.
    Descriptions now wrap at 80 characters for better readability.
  * No breaking changes to runtime parsing behavior.

 -- rail5 <andrew@rail5.org>  Fri, 06 Feb 2026 14:31:15 +0800

